==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imposthume
<hw>Im*post"hume</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A corruption of
<ets>aposteme</ets>. See <er>Aposteme</er>.]</ety> <def>A collection of
pus or purulent matter in any part of an animal body; an
abscess.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imposthume</ent>⟦br⟧

